<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-16457] Hint messages are incorrectly re-serialized for filtering in in-jvm dtests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16457</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hint messages for dropped tables can still be dispatched, but they&#8217;re ignored on the receiving side all usual code paths. Since we&#8217;re attempting to re-serialize hint message for dropped table in in-jvm tests, we exercise path that is impossible in regular code, and for which there is no protocol specification. &lt;/p&gt;


